<paragraph blockId="4.[151,581,1265,1325]" box="[151,323,1300,1325]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,231,1300,1325]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1920,1943]" captionTargetBox="[178,1421,195,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[178,1421,195,1904]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Trichromothrips genus-group species. Trichromothrips species 1–11: (1) T. moundi female. (2) T. moundi male. (3) T. albus. female (4) T. guizhouensis sp.n. female (5) T. indicus female. (6) T. elegans female. (7) T. elegans male. (8) T. trifasciatus female. (9) T. crispator female. (10) T. antidesmae sp.n. female. (11) T. assamensis female. (12) Trachynotothrips striatus female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2618151/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Figs 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[243,315,1300,1325]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 22–30. Trichromothrips species. T. guizhouensis sp.n. 22–26: (22) Head and pronotum. (23) Abdominal tergites III–X. (24) Mesonotum and metanotum. (25) Fore wing. (26) Antennae. T. antidesmae sp.n. 27–30: (27) Head and pronotum. (28) Male abdominal tergites IX–X. (29) Fore wing. (30) Antennae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2618155/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">22–26</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1372,2009]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis box="[151,374,1372,1397]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Female macroptera</emphasis>
. Body bicolored (
<figureCitation box="[583,654,1372,1397]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1920,1943]" captionTargetBox="[178,1421,195,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[178,1421,195,1904]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Trichromothrips genus-group species. Trichromothrips species 1–11: (1) T. moundi female. (2) T. moundi male. (3) T. albus. female (4) T. guizhouensis sp.n. female (5) T. indicus female. (6) T. elegans female. (7) T. elegans male. (8) T. trifasciatus female. (9) T. crispator female. (10) T. antidesmae sp.n. female. (11) T. assamensis female. (12) Trachynotothrips striatus female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2618151/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); head uniformly dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[1009,1095,1372,1397]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 22–30. Trichromothrips species. T. guizhouensis sp.n. 22–26: (22) Head and pronotum. (23) Abdominal tergites III–X. (24) Mesonotum and metanotum. (25) Fore wing. (26) Antennae. T. antidesmae sp.n. 27–30: (27) Head and pronotum. (28) Male abdominal tergites IX–X. (29) Fore wing. (30) Antennae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2618155/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
); antennal segments I–II dark brown, III–V yellow with the apical third brown, VI–VIII pale brown, VIII with apex slightly paler(
<figureCitation box="[1338,1423,1407,1432]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 22–30. Trichromothrips species. T. guizhouensis sp.n. 22–26: (22) Head and pronotum. (23) Abdominal tergites III–X. (24) Mesonotum and metanotum. (25) Fore wing. (26) Antennae. T. antidesmae sp.n. 27–30: (27) Head and pronotum. (28) Male abdominal tergites IX–X. (29) Fore wing. (30) Antennae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2618155/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
); pronotum with dark brown lateral stripes, median triangular pale area not reaching anterior margin(
<figureCitation box="[1287,1369,1444,1469]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 22–30. Trichromothrips species. T. guizhouensis sp.n. 22–26: (22) Head and pronotum. (23) Abdominal tergites III–X. (24) Mesonotum and metanotum. (25) Fore wing. (26) Antennae. T. antidesmae sp.n. 27–30: (27) Head and pronotum. (28) Male abdominal tergites IX–X. (29) Fore wing. (30) Antennae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2618155/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
); fore wing including clavus brown with a small spot near the base(
<figureCitation box="[835,915,1479,1504]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 22–30. Trichromothrips species. T. guizhouensis sp.n. 22–26: (22) Head and pronotum. (23) Abdominal tergites III–X. (24) Mesonotum and metanotum. (25) Fore wing. (26) Antennae. T. antidesmae sp.n. 27–30: (27) Head and pronotum. (28) Male abdominal tergites IX–X. (29) Fore wing. (30) Antennae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2618155/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
); all legs yellowish white; abdominal tergite II with a small pale brown patch in middle, III–VI yellowish white each with an inverted trapezoidal-shaped area in the middle, VII–IX dark brown, X yellowish brown with apex pale(
<figureCitation box="[909,981,1551,1576]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1920,1943]" captionTargetBox="[178,1421,195,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[178,1421,195,1904]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Trichromothrips genus-group species. Trichromothrips species 1–11: (1) T. moundi female. (2) T. moundi male. (3) T. albus. female (4) T. guizhouensis sp.n. female (5) T. indicus female. (6) T. elegans female. (7) T. elegans male. (8) T. trifasciatus female. (9) T. crispator female. (10) T. antidesmae sp.n. female. (11) T. assamensis female. (12) Trachynotothrips striatus female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2618151/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Figs 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[993,1024,1551,1576]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 22–30. Trichromothrips species. T. guizhouensis sp.n. 22–26: (22) Head and pronotum. (23) Abdominal tergites III–X. (24) Mesonotum and metanotum. (25) Fore wing. (26) Antennae. T. antidesmae sp.n. 27–30: (27) Head and pronotum. (28) Male abdominal tergites IX–X. (29) Fore wing. (30) Antennae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2618155/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">25</figureCitation>
); body setae brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1372,2009]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[280,368,1588,1613]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 22–30. Trichromothrips species. T. guizhouensis sp.n. 22–26: (22) Head and pronotum. (23) Abdominal tergites III–X. (24) Mesonotum and metanotum. (25) Fore wing. (26) Antennae. T. antidesmae sp.n. 27–30: (27) Head and pronotum. (28) Male abdominal tergites IX–X. (29) Fore wing. (30) Antennae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2618155/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) longer than wide, with a fairly long neck-like constriction and transverse striae behind compound eyes; ocellar setae III situated at tangent of posterior margin of hind ocelli; six pairs of postocular setae present, V far from compound eyes. Antennal segments III–VI with microtrichia (
<figureCitation box="[1089,1174,1660,1685]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 22–30. Trichromothrips species. T. guizhouensis sp.n. 22–26: (22) Head and pronotum. (23) Abdominal tergites III–X. (24) Mesonotum and metanotum. (25) Fore wing. (26) Antennae. T. antidesmae sp.n. 27–30: (27) Head and pronotum. (28) Male abdominal tergites IX–X. (29) Fore wing. (30) Antennae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2618155/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
), VIII longer than VII. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[277,359,1695,1720]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 22–30. Trichromothrips species. T. guizhouensis sp.n. 22–26: (22) Head and pronotum. (23) Abdominal tergites III–X. (24) Mesonotum and metanotum. (25) Fore wing. (26) Antennae. T. antidesmae sp.n. 27–30: (27) Head and pronotum. (28) Male abdominal tergites IX–X. (29) Fore wing. (30) Antennae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2618155/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) wider than long, smooth with about 16–18 discal setae, inner posteroangular setae longer than outer, two pairs of posteromarginal setae present. Mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[893,979,1732,1757]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 22–30. Trichromothrips species. T. guizhouensis sp.n. 22–26: (22) Head and pronotum. (23) Abdominal tergites III–X. (24) Mesonotum and metanotum. (25) Fore wing. (26) Antennae. T. antidesmae sp.n. 27–30: (27) Head and pronotum. (28) Male abdominal tergites IX–X. (29) Fore wing. (30) Antennae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2618155/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
) anterior smooth with some transverse striate sculpture near posterior margin, CPS absent anteromedially; median pair of setae situated in front of submedian pairs. Metascutum (
<figureCitation box="[508,592,1804,1829]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 22–30. Trichromothrips species. T. guizhouensis sp.n. 22–26: (22) Head and pronotum. (23) Abdominal tergites III–X. (24) Mesonotum and metanotum. (25) Fore wing. (26) Antennae. T. antidesmae sp.n. 27–30: (27) Head and pronotum. (28) Male abdominal tergites IX–X. (29) Fore wing. (30) Antennae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2618155/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
) smooth medially but sculptured longitudinally at each side, CPS absent; median pair of setae close to anterior margin. Prosternal ferna undivided. Metaepimeron without setae. Mesosternum with sternopleural sutures; only mesothoracic endofurca present. Fore wing first vein usually with 7 basal and 2 discal setae, second vein with 17 setae; clavus usually with 3–5 veinal and 1 discal setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1372,2009]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,824]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="84" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
Abdominal tergites with transverse striae laterally and a few striae at anterior margin; tergites II–VII (
<figureCitation box="[1346,1428,1948,1973]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 22–30. Trichromothrips species. T. guizhouensis sp.n. 22–26: (22) Head and pronotum. (23) Abdominal tergites III–X. (24) Mesonotum and metanotum. (25) Fore wing. (26) Antennae. T. antidesmae sp.n. 27–30: (27) Head and pronotum. (28) Male abdominal tergites IX–X. (29) Fore wing. (30) Antennae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2618155/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
) with three setae (S3 to S5 setae) arranged in a straight line along lateral margin; S4 minute on tergites V–VIII; tergite IX without CPS; sternites without discal setae, II–VII each with 3 pairs of posteromarginal setae, VII with all three pairs of setae inserted ahead of posterior margin.
</paragraph>
