<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="84" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,824]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,548,573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Comments.</emphasis>
This new species runs to 
<emphasis box="[636,703,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">bellus</emphasis>
in the key provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bhatti, J. S." box="[982,1137,548,573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="1 - 65" refId="ref7055" refString="Bhatti, J. S. (2000) Revision of Trichromothrips and related genera (Terebrantia: Thripidae), Oriental Insects, 34 (1), 1 - 65. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.2000.10417252" type="journal article" year="2000">Bhatti (2000)</bibRefCitation>
, but is distinguished from 
<emphasis box="[151,218,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">bellus</emphasis>
by the presence of the mesothoracic endofurca, S4 minute on tergites V–VIII and abdominal tergites VII–IX dark brown. It is closely related to 
<emphasis box="[544,634,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">dorsalis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Masumoto, M. &amp; Okajima, S." box="[649,971,620,645]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="45 - 50" refId="ref7367" refString="Masumoto, M. &amp; Okajima, S. (2011) A new species of the genus Trichromothrips (Thysanoptera, Thripidae) from bamboo in Thailand, Malaysia and Vietnam. Zootaxa, 3118, 45 - 50." type="journal article" year="2011">Masumoto &amp; Okajima 2011</bibRefCitation>
), but can be distinguished by head with a long neck-like constriction, abdominal tergites III–VI each with an inverted trapezoidal brown patch in the middle and tergites VII–IX dark brown (in 
<emphasis box="[546,636,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">dorsalis</emphasis>
head slightly concave behind compound eyes, abdominal tergites I–VII yellowish white with III–VII each with a transverse diamond-shaped dark area in middle, VIII–IX dark brown). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Masumoto, M. &amp; Okajima, S." box="[308,663,764,789]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="45 - 50" refId="ref7367" refString="Masumoto, M. &amp; Okajima, S. (2011) A new species of the genus Trichromothrips (Thysanoptera, Thripidae) from bamboo in Thailand, Malaysia and Vietnam. Zootaxa, 3118, 45 - 50." type="journal article" year="2011">Masumoto and Okajima (2011)</bibRefCitation>
this species may belong to 
<emphasis box="[980,1047,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">bellus</emphasis>
-section together with 
<emphasis box="[1302,1343,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">alis</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[1358,1428,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">arorai</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[151,241,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">dorsalis</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[255,340,799,824]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Trichromothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis box="[255,340,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[395,496,801,824]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">taiwanus</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
